<h1>Competition Team Information</h1>
<h2><i>Carnegie Mellon University Ballroom Dance Club Competition Team Practice Policy</i></h2>
<p>Costs involved with a competition include registration, travel, and lodging-the club subsidizes a fraction of the cost (based on how many attend) so that it is more affordable for all to go. Since you are more prepared to do well at a competition and enjoy it more when you have practiced sufficiently, the club wants to reward your practice time invested by subsidizing your trip! Subsidies work as follows:</p><br /><br />

<p>To get subsidized, you must practice for at least 12 hours in the month before a competition, 6 of them with the team, 3 of them with your partner.</p><br />
**NOTE: Lessons and formation <b>do not</b> count as practice! Thus, the following times are free each week:<br />
<b>Mondays 10-11 PM<br />
Wednesdays 10-11 PM<br />
Saturdays 12:30 - 2:30 PM<br />
Sundays 12 - 2 PM</b><br />

<p>You are allowed to practice outside of these times, but must log those hours in the google form.</p><br /><br />

